Following the earthquake in the southwestern Sichuan Province, Belgian Foreign Minister Karel De Gucht has sent a message of condolence to his Chinese counterpart Yang Jiechi expressing his sympathy with the victims of Monday's earthquake that killed more than 8,600 people, the Belgian Foreign Ministry said in a statement.
Vietnam has expressed deep sympathies to China at huge losses caused by an earthquake in China's southwestern Sichuan province, Vietnam News Agency reported Tuesday.
A strong earthquake measuring 7.8 magnitude struck Wenchuan county of Sichuan alone on Monday's, leaving at least 12,000 people died and thousands more injured.
